### Configure Root-level Admin Route in PayloadCMS

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/admin/overview.mdx

This code snippet demonstrates how to configure the PayloadCMS Admin Panel to mount at the root level of your application by setting the `routes.admin` property to '/'. This change requires a corresponding adjustment in your project's file structure, specifically removing the 'admin' directory, to ensure proper routing and avoid conflicts.

```ts
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'

const config = buildConfig({
  // ...
  routes: {
    admin: '/', // highlight-line
  },
})
```

--------------------------------

