### Configure Admin Panel User Collection in Payload

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/admin/overview.mdx

This snippet demonstrates how to specify which auth-enabled collection can log into the Payload CMS Admin Panel. It uses the `admin.user` key within the `buildConfig` function to set the collection slug, ensuring only users from the specified collection (e.g., 'admins') have access. This prevents other authenticated users, such as 'customers', from logging into the admin interface.

```ts
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'

const config = buildConfig({
  // ...
  admin: {
    user: 'admins' // highlight-line
  }
})
```

