### Configure Payload CMS Admin Panel with Custom Components and Views (TS)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/tools/claude-plugin/skills/payload/reference/ADVANCED.md

This TypeScript configuration demonstrates how to customize the Payload CMS admin panel. It registers React components to be displayed `beforeDashboard` and `beforeLogin`, and defines a new custom view accessible via a specific path, pointing to a custom component.

```ts
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'

export default buildConfig({
  admin: {
    components: {
      beforeDashboard: ['/components/BeforeDashboard'],
      beforeLogin: ['/components/BeforeLogin'],
      views: {
        custom: {
          Component: '/views/Custom',
          path: '/custom',
        },
      },
    },
  },
  collections: [],
  secret: process.env.PAYLOAD_SECRET || '',
})
```

