### Replace a Built-in Payload Admin View with TypeScript

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/custom-components/custom-views.mdx

This configuration snippet demonstrates how to replace a default Admin Panel view, specifically the dashboard, with a custom React component. It uses the `admin.components.views` property in the Payload configuration to map the 'dashboard' key to a custom `Component` path.

```ts
import { buildConfig } from 'payload'

const config = buildConfig({
  // ...
  admin: {
    components: {
      views: {
        // highlight-start
        dashboard: {
          Component: '/path/to/MyCustomDashboard',
        },
        // highlight-end
      },
    },
  },
})
```
